        <answer>
          <p>      <m>\tta\ttb = \bbm 0\amp 0\amp 4\\  6\amp 4\amp -2\\  2\amp -4\amp -6\ebm</m>,
            <m>\ttb\tta = \bbm 2\amp -2\amp 6\\  2\amp 2\amp 4\\  4\amp 0\amp -6\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </answer>
      </exercise>

      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <m>\tta = \bbm -4\amp 3\amp 3\\  -5\amp -1\amp -5\\  -5\amp 0\amp -1\ebm</m>,
            <m>\ttb =  \bbm 0\amp 5\amp 0\\  -5\amp -4\amp 3\\  5\amp -4\amp 3\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p>      <m>\tta\ttb = \bbm 0\amp -44\amp 18\\  -20\amp -1\amp -18\\  -5\amp -21\amp -3\ebm</m>,
            <m>\ttb\tta = \bbm -25\amp -5\amp -25\\  25\amp -11\amp 2\\  -15\amp 19\amp 32\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </answer>
      </exercise>

      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <m>\tta = \bbm -4\amp -1\amp 3\\  2\amp -3\amp 5\\  1\amp 5\amp 3\ebm</m>,
            <m>\ttb =  \bbm -2\amp 4\amp 3\\  -1\amp 1\amp -1\\  4\amp 0\amp 2\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p>      <m>\tta\ttb = \bbm 21\amp -17\amp -5\\  19\amp 5\amp 19\\  5\amp 9\amp 4\ebm</m>,
            <m>\ttb\tta = \bbm 19\amp 5\amp 23\\  5\amp -7\amp -1\\  -14\amp 6\amp 18\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </answer>
      </exercise>

    </exercisegroup>

    <exercisegroup cols="2">

      <introduction>
        <p>
          A <em>diagonal</em> matrix <m>\ttd</m> and a matrix <m>\tta</m> are given.
          Find the products <m>\ttd\tta</m> and <m>\tta\ttd</m>, where possible.
        </p>
      </introduction>

      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <m>\ttd = \bbm -1\amp 0\amp 0\\  0\amp 2\amp 0\\  0\amp 0\amp 3\ebm</m>,
            <m>\tta = \bbm 1\amp 2\amp 3\\  4\amp 5\amp 6\\  7\amp 8\amp 9\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p>      <m>\ttd\tta= \bbm -1\amp 4\amp 9\\  -4\amp 10\amp 18\\  -7\amp 16\amp 27\ebm</m>,
            <m>\tta\ttd = \bbm -1\amp -2\amp -3\\  8\amp 10\amp 12\\  21\amp 24\amp 27\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </answer>
      </exercise>

      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <m>\ttd = \bbm 1\amp 1\amp 1\\  2\amp 2\amp 2\\  -3\amp -3\amp -3\ebm</m>,
            <m>\tta = \bbm 2\amp 0\amp 0\\  0\amp -3\amp 0\\  0\amp 0\amp 5\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p>      <m>\ttd\tta= \bbm 2\amp 2\amp 2\\  -6\amp -6\amp -6\\  -15\amp -15\amp -15\ebm</m>,
            <m>\tta\ttd =  \bbm 2\amp -3\amp 5\\  4\amp -6\amp 10\\  -6\amp 9\amp -15\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </answer>
      </exercise>

      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <m>\ttd = \bbm 3\amp 0\\  0\amp -1\ebm</m>,
            <m>\tta = \bbm 2\amp 4\\  6\amp 8\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p>      <m>\ttd\tta= \bbm 6\amp -4\\  18\amp -8\ebm</m>,
            <m>\tta\ttd =  \bbm 6\amp 12\\  -6\amp -8\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </answer>
      </exercise>

      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <m>\ttd = \bbm 4\amp 0\\  0\amp -3\ebm</m>,
            <m>\tta = \bbm 1\amp 2\\  1\amp 2\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p>
            <m>\ttd\tta= \bbm 4\amp -6\\  4\amp -6\ebm</m>,
            <m>\tta\ttd =  \bbm 4\amp 8\\  -3\amp -6\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </answer>
      </exercise>

      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <m>\ttd = \bbm d_1\amp 0\\  0\amp d_2\ebm</m>,
            <m>\tta = \bbm a\amp b\\  c\amp d\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p>
            <m>\ttd\tta= \bbm d_1a\amp d_1b\\  d_2c\amp d_2d\ebm</m>,
            <m>\tta\ttd =  \bbm d_1a\amp d_2b\\  d_1c\amp d_2d\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </answer>
      </exercise>

      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <m>\ttd = \bbm d_1\amp 0\amp 0\\  0\amp d_2\amp 0\\  0\amp 0\amp d_3\ebm</m>,
            <m>\tta = \bbm a\amp b\amp c\\  d\amp e\amp f\\  g\amp h\amp i\ebm </m>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p>
            <m>\ttd\tta= \bbm d_1a\amp d_1b\amp d_1c\\  d_2d\amp d_2e\amp d_2f\\  d_3g\amp d_3h\amp d_3i\ebm</m>,
            <m>\tta\ttd =  \bbm d_1a\amp d_2b\amp d_3c\\  d_1d\amp d_2e\amp d_3f\\  d_1g\amp d_2h\amp d_3i\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </answer>
      </exercise>
    </exercisegroup>

    <exercisegroup cols="2">

      <introduction>
        <p>
          A matrix <m>\tta</m> and a vector <m>\vx</m> are given. Find the product <m>\tta\vx</m>.
        </p>
      </introduction>

      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <m>\tta = \bbm 2\amp 3\\  1\amp -1\ebm</m>,
            <m>\vx = \bbm 4\\  9\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p>
            <m>\tta\vx= \bbm 35\\  -5\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </answer>
      </exercise>

      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <m>\tta =   \bbm -1\amp 4\\  7\amp 3\ebm</m>,
            <m>\vx = \bbm 2\\  -1\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p>
            <m>\tta\vx= \bbm -6\\  11\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </answer>
      </exercise>

      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <m>\tta =   \bbm 2\amp 0\amp 3\\  1\amp 1\amp 1\\  3\amp -1\amp 2\ebm</m>,
            <m>\vx = \bbm 1\\  4\\  2\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p>
            <m>\tta\vx= \bbm 8\\  7\\  3\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </answer>
      </exercise>

      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <m>\tta = \bbm -2\amp 0\amp 3\\  1\amp 1\amp -2\\  4\amp 2\amp -1\ebm</m>,
            <m>\vx = \bbm 4\\  3\\  1\ebm </m>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p>
            <m>\tta\vx= \bbm -5\\  5\\  21\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </answer>
      </exercise>

      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <m>\tta = \bbm 1\amp 2\amp 3\\  1\amp 0\amp 2\\  2\amp 3\amp 1\ebm</m>,
            <m>\vx = \bbm x_1\\  x_2\\  x_3\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p>
            <m>\tta\vx= \bbm x_1+2x_2+3x_3\\  x_1+2x_3\\  2x_1+3x_2+x_3\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </answer>
      </exercise>

      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            <m>\tta = \bbm 2\amp -1\\   4\amp 3\ebm</m>,
            <m>\vx = \bbm x_1\\  x_2\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p>
            <m>\tta\vx= \bbm2x_1-x_2\\  4x_1+3x_2\ebm</m>
          </p>
        </answer>
      </exercise>

    </exercisegroup>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Let <m>\tta = \bbm 0 \amp 1\\1 \amp 0\ebm</m>. Find <m>\tta^2</m> and <m>\tta^3</m>.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>\tta^2 = \bbm 1 \amp 0\\0 \amp 1\ebm</m>; <m>\tta^3 = \bbm 0\amp 1\\1\amp 0\ebm</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Let <m>\tta = \bbm 2 \amp 0\\0 \amp 3\ebm</m>. Find <m>\tta^2</m> and <m>\tta^3</m>.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>\tta^2 = \bbm 4 \amp 0\\0 \amp 9\ebm</m>; <m>\tta^3 = \bbm 8\amp 0\\0\amp 27\ebm</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Let <m>\tta = \bbm -1 \amp 0 \amp 0\\0\amp 3\amp 0\\0\amp 0\amp 5\ebm</m>. Find <m>\tta^2</m> and <m>\tta^3</m>.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>\tta^2 = \bbm 1 \amp 0 \amp 0\\0\amp 9\amp 0\\0\amp 0\amp 25\ebm</m>; <m>\tta^3 = \bbm -1\amp 0\amp 0\\0\amp 27\amp 0\\0\amp 0\amp 125\ebm</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Let <m>\tta = \bbm 0 \amp 1 \amp 0\\0\amp 0\amp 1\\1\amp 0\amp 0\ebm</m>. Find <m>\tta^2</m> and <m>\tta^3</m>.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>\tta^2 = \bbm 0 \amp 0 \amp 1\\1\amp 0\amp 0\\0\amp 1\amp 0\ebm</m>; <m>\tta^3 = \bbm 1\amp 0\amp 0\\0\amp 1\amp 0\\0\amp 0\amp 1\ebm</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Let <m>\tta = \bbm 0 \amp 0 \amp 1\\0\amp 0\amp 0\\0\amp 1\amp 0\ebm</m>. Find <m>\tta^2</m> and <m>\tta^3</m>.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>\tta^2 = \bbm 0 \amp 1 \amp 0\\0\amp 0\amp 0\\0\amp 0\amp 0\ebm</m>; <m>\tta^3 = \bbm 0\amp 0\amp 0\\0\amp 0\amp 0\\0\amp 0\amp 0\ebm</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          In the text we state that <m>(\tta+\ttb)^2 \neq \tta^2+2\tta\ttb+\ttb^2</m>. We investigate that claim here.
          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>
                Let <m>\tta = \bbm 5\amp 3\\  -3\amp -2\ebm</m> and let <m>\ttb = \bbm -5 \amp -5\  -2 \amp 1\ebm</m>.
                Compute <m>\tta+\ttb</m>.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Find <m>(\tta+\ttb)^2</m> by using your answer from (a).
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Compute <m>\tta^2+2\tta\ttb+\ttb^2</m>.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Are the results from (a) and (b) the same?
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Carefully expand the expression
                <me>
                  (\tta+\ttb)^2 = (\tta+\ttb)(\tta+\ttb)
                </me>
                and show why this is not equal to <m>\tta^2+2\tta\ttb+\ttb^2</m>.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>
                <m>\bbm 0\amp -2\\-5\amp -1\ebm</m>
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                <m>\bbm 10\amp 2\\  5\amp 11\ebm</m>
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                <m>\bbm -11 \amp -15\  37 \amp 32\ebm</m>
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                No.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                <m>(\tta+\ttb)(\tta + \ttb) = \tta\tta + \tta\ttb + \ttb\tta + \ttb\ttb = \tta^2+\tta\ttb+\ttb\tta+\ttb^2</m>.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>
  </exercises>
</section>